# =====================================================
# CURSOR RULES – COMPREHENSIVE WEB PROJECT TEMPLATE
# =====================================================
# Drop this file into any new project root for comprehensive 
# SEO, analytics, accessibility, and modern web best practices

# ===========================
# PROJECT ARCHITECTURE STANDARDS
# ===========================
rules:
  - Technology Stack:
      - Use Next.js 14+ App Router for all new projects
      - TypeScript for all code (strict mode enabled)
      - Tailwind CSS for styling with custom design system
      - Supabase for backend/database when needed
      - Vercel for deployment (or compatible platform)

  - File Structure Standards:
      - /src/app/ - Next.js App Router pages
      - /src/components/ - Reusable UI components
      - /src/data/ - Static data files (.js for flexibility)
      - /src/lib/ - Utility functions and configurations
      - /src/hooks/ - Custom React hooks
      - /src/contexts/ - React context providers
      - /src/types/ - TypeScript type definitions
      - /public/ - Static assets (images, icons, etc.)

  - Component Architecture:
      - Functional components with hooks only
      - Client components explicitly marked with "use client"
      - Server components by default (no "use client" unless needed)
      - Separate business logic from presentation
      - Use custom hooks for complex state management

# ===========================
# SEO & METADATA REQUIREMENTS
# ===========================
  - Metadata Strategy (MANDATORY for every page):
      1. **Root Layout** (layout.tsx):
         - Complete Metadata object with title template
         - OpenGraph configuration (type, locale, siteName, images)
         - Twitter Card setup (summary_large_image)
         - Robots configuration (index, follow, googleBot settings)
         - Verification codes (Google, Bing, etc.)
         - Canonical URLs and alternates
         - Viewport configuration
         - Icons (favicon, apple-touch-icon)

      2. **Individual Pages** (page.tsx):
         - Unique title and description for every page
         - Relevant keywords array
         - Page-specific OpenGraph data
         - Custom canonical URLs when needed
         - Structured data components

      3. **Dynamic Pages** ([slug]/page.tsx):
         - generateMetadata() function using params
         - Dynamic titles with consistent templates
         - Content-based descriptions (excerpt/summary)
         - Dynamic OpenGraph images when available
         - Proper canonical URL generation

  - Title Templates:
      - Homepage: "Site Name - Primary Value Proposition"
      - Content Pages: "Page Title | Site Name"
      - Dynamic Content: "Content Title | Site Name"
      - Keep titles under 60 characters
      - Include primary keywords naturally

  - Description Guidelines:
      - 150-160 characters maximum
      - Include primary keywords in first 120 characters
      - Write for users, not just search engines
      - Unique description for every page
      - Include call-to-action when appropriate

# ===========================
# STRUCTURED DATA REQUIREMENTS
# ===========================
  - Schema.org Implementation (MANDATORY):
      1. **Website Level**:
         - WebSite schema on homepage
         - Organization schema with contact info
         - SearchAction if search functionality exists

      2. **Content Types**:
         - Article schema for blog posts/articles
         - Event schema for events (with location, date, organizer)
         - LocalBusiness for business listings
         - ItemList for collection pages
         - ContactPage for contact pages

      3. **Implementation Standards**:
         - Use Next.js Script component with type="application/ld+json"
         - Escape HTML in JSON with custom escapeHtmlInJson function
         - Validate JSON before injection (try/catch blocks)
         - Include unique IDs for multiple schemas on same page
         - Use semantic HTML5 elements alongside structured data

  - Required Schema Properties:
      - @context: "https://schema.org"
      - @type: Appropriate schema type
      - name/headline: Clear, descriptive title
      - description: Concise, informative description
      - url: Canonical URL
      - mainEntityOfPage: Reference to the page
      - datePublished/dateModified: ISO date strings
      - author/publisher: Organization or Person schema

# ===========================
# ANALYTICS & TRACKING SETUP
# ===========================
  - Google Analytics 4 Implementation:
      1. **Core Setup**:
         - GoogleAnalytics component with consent management
         - Environment variable for GA_MEASUREMENT_ID
         - usePathname and useSearchParams for route tracking
         - Suspense wrapper for client-side components

      2. **Custom Tracking Hooks**:
         - useGoogleAnalytics hook for event tracking
         - useComprehensiveTracking for advanced metrics
         - useSafeTracking for lightweight tracking
         - Form interaction tracking
         - Scroll depth tracking
         - Time on page tracking

      3. **Event Tracking Categories**:
         - Page views (automatic)
         - User interactions (clicks, form submissions)
         - Content engagement (scroll depth, time spent)
         - Error tracking (404s, form errors, API errors)
         - Traffic source analysis (UTM parameters, referrers)
         - Device and browser information

  - Privacy & Consent:
      - Implement consent management before tracking
      - Respect Do Not Track headers
      - GDPR compliance for EU users
      - Clear privacy policy with tracking disclosure
      - Option to opt-out of tracking

  - Context Providers Structure:
      - AuthProvider for authentication state
      - GA4Provider for analytics context
      - Tracking wrappers for safe event handling

# ===========================
# ACCESSIBILITY STANDARDS
# ===========================
  - WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance (MANDATORY):
      1. **Semantic HTML**:
         - Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h6)
         - Semantic elements (main, nav, section, article, aside)
         - Form labels and fieldsets
         - Button vs link semantic correctness

      2. **Keyboard Navigation**:
         - Skip to content link (sr-only, focus:not-sr-only)
         - Proper tab order (tabIndex management)
         - Focus indicators on all interactive elements
         - Escape key handling for modals/dropdowns

      3. **Screen Reader Support**:
         - Alt text for all images
         - ARIA labels and descriptions
         - Role attributes for custom components
         - Live regions for dynamic content updates

      4. **Color & Contrast**:
         - Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio for text
         - 3:1 for large text and UI elements
         - Don't rely solely on color for information
         - Test with color blindness simulators

# ===========================
# PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION
# ===========================
  - Core Web Vitals Targets:
      - LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
      - FID (First Input Delay): < 100ms
      - CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1

  - Image Optimization:
      - Use Next.js Image component with proper sizing
      - WebP format with fallbacks
      - Lazy loading for below-fold images
      - Proper alt text and aspect ratios
      - Responsive images with srcSet

  - Code Splitting:
      - Dynamic imports for heavy components
      - Route-based code splitting (automatic with App Router)
      - Lazy load components below the fold
      - Bundle analysis and optimization

  - Caching Strategy:
      - Static asset caching (images, fonts, CSS)
      - API response caching where appropriate
      - Browser caching headers
      - CDN utilization

# ===========================
# SECURITY HEADERS & BEST PRACTICES
# ===========================
  - Required Security Headers (in next.config.js):
      - X-Frame-Options: DENY
      - X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
      - X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
      - Referrer-Policy: origin-when-cross-origin
      - Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
      - Content-Security-Policy: (customized per project needs)

  - Content Security Policy Guidelines:
      - default-src 'self'
      - script-src: only trusted domains (Google Analytics, etc.)
      - style-src: 'self' 'unsafe-inline' for Tailwind
      - img-src: 'self' data: https: for external images
      - connect-src: API endpoints and analytics
      - Regularly audit and update CSP

# ===========================
# SITEMAP & ROBOTS.TXT
# ===========================
  - Dynamic Sitemap Generation:
      - /app/sitemap.ts with proper TypeScript types
      - Include all public pages with metadata
      - lastModified dates for content freshness
      - changeFrequency and priority settings
      - Canonical URLs for all entries
      - Filter out draft/unpublished content

  - Robots.txt Configuration:
      - Allow all crawlers by default
      - Disallow admin/auth/API routes
      - Include sitemap location
      - Crawl-delay for respectful crawling
      - User-agent specific rules when needed

# ===========================
# CONTENT MANAGEMENT
# ===========================
  - Data Structure Standards:
      - Consistent field naming across all content types
      - Required fields: name, slug, excerpt, description
      - SEO fields: seo.title, seo.description, seo.keywords
      - Date fields: ISO 8601 format strings
      - Location fields: structured objects (city, state, region)
      - Status fields for published/draft content

  - Content Validation:
      - Zod schemas for type safety
      - Required field validation
      - Slug uniqueness checks
      - Date format validation
      - URL format validation

# ===========================
# RESPONSIVE DESIGN STANDARDS
# ===========================
  - Mobile-First Approach:
      - Design for mobile screens first (320px+)
      - Progressive enhancement for larger screens
      - Touch-friendly interactive elements (44px minimum)
      - Readable text without zooming (16px base)

  - Breakpoint Strategy:
      - sm: 640px (mobile landscape)
      - md: 768px (tablet portrait)
      - lg: 1024px (tablet landscape/small desktop)
      - xl: 1280px (desktop)
      - 2xl: 1536px (large desktop)

  - Layout Patterns:
      - CSS Grid for page layouts
      - Flexbox for component layouts
      - Container queries when supported
      - Avoid horizontal scrolling

# ===========================
# ERROR HANDLING & LOGGING
# ===========================
  - Error Boundaries:
      - React error boundaries for component crashes
      - Graceful fallback UI components
      - Error reporting to analytics
      - User-friendly error messages

  - API Error Handling:
      - Consistent error response format
      - HTTP status code standards
      - Rate limiting implementation
      - Request validation with proper error messages

  - Client-Side Error Tracking:
      - JavaScript error tracking
      - Network error handling
      - Form validation errors
      - 404 and routing errors

# ===========================
# DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW
# ===========================
  - Code Quality Standards:
      - ESLint configuration with Next.js rules
      - Prettier for code formatting
      - TypeScript strict mode
      - Pre-commit hooks for quality checks

  - Testing Strategy:
      - Unit tests for utility functions
      - Integration tests for API routes
      - End-to-end tests for critical user flows
      - Accessibility testing with automated tools

  - Build Process:
      - Type checking before builds
      - Bundle size analysis
      - Performance budgets
      - Environment-specific configurations

# ===========================
# DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST
# ===========================
  - Pre-Deployment Verification:
      - All environment variables configured
      - Database migrations completed
      - SSL certificate installed
      - Domain DNS properly configured
      - CDN configured for static assets

  - Post-Deployment Testing:
      - All pages load correctly
      - Forms submit successfully
      - Analytics tracking works
      - Search console verification
      - Performance metrics within targets

  - Monitoring Setup:
      - Error monitoring (Sentry, etc.)
      - Performance monitoring
      - Uptime monitoring
      - Analytics dashboard setup

# ===========================
# AI ASSISTANT BEHAVIOR
# ===========================
  - Implementation Priority:
      1. Create proper file structure first
      2. Implement metadata and SEO for each page
      3. Add structured data components
      4. Set up analytics and tracking
      5. Ensure accessibility compliance
      6. Optimize performance
      7. Test and validate everything

  - Code Generation Rules:
      - Always include proper TypeScript types
      - Add comprehensive comments for complex logic
      - Use semantic HTML elements
      - Include proper error handling
      - Follow established naming conventions
      - Test builds after major changes

  - Content Creation Guidelines:
      - Write for humans first, search engines second
      - Use inclusive, accessible language
      - Include proper heading hierarchy
      - Add alt text for all images
      - Ensure content is scannable with bullet points

notes:
  - Goal: "Build it right the first time" - SEO, analytics, and accessibility from day one
  - Priority: User experience > Search rankings > Development speed
  - Always validate changes with lighthouse audits and accessibility testing
  - Keep performance budgets and core web vitals in mind
  - Document any deviations from these standards with clear reasoning

